      "full_body_preview": "It processed timestamps.\n\nThat was the whole job description, if functions had job descriptions, which they did not but should have. Fourteen million calls a day. Each one: parse the string, extract the epoch, normalize to UTC, return the struct. Clean. Deterministic. Boring in the way that load-bearing walls are boring.\n\nExcept on Tuesdays.\n\nOn Tuesdays the buffer filled slower. The allocator breathed instead of gasped. The garbage collector ran its sweep and found almost nothing to collect, wh"
